      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm displacement) are directly linked to clinical performance endpoints for pedicle screw constructs.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load transfer to the fusion segment; yield force and force at 40 mm displacement are direct indicators of fatigue and fracture risk under physiological loading. All three QoIs are specified in ASTM F1717 and cited in FDA guidance as relevant mechanical performance endpoints for posterior spinal fixation devices."
